      ''
      '  Index Field(s) or Expression:'
      '  You can define indexes for the table by clicking the button "New".'
      '  In the new window, select one field and click the button "Add".'
      '  Enter a name for the index. You can insert an expression between'
      '  fields (like Field1 + Field2 or like DTOS(DateField)+StringField).'
      '  You can also set the options for the index (primary, unique, etc...).'
      '  Finally confirm by clicking the "Save" button.'
      '  Expressions:'
      '  Expressions are used in indexes. When adding an index, you need to'
      '  supply an index expression.'
      '  Supported functions:'
      '  UPPER(stringfield)'
      '  Returns the uppercase equivalent of stringfield'
      '  LOWER(stringfield)'
      '  Returns the lowercase equivalent of stringfield'
      '  DTOS(datefield)'
      '  Converts datefield to a string with representation YYYYMMDD'
      '  To set an index on a date/time field, use DTOS function.'
      '  STR( numericfield,size,precision )'
      '  Converts a number field to a string with optional size and precision.'
      '  SUBSTR(stringfield,index,count)'
      '  Index expressions that return a string may be maximum 100 characters long.'
    )
